author: The Current
description:
Watch jeremy messersmith's solo acoustic performance of "Twenty Years"
Support The Current: https://support.mpr.org/youtube or hit the Thanks button

In his song "Twenty Years," Minnesota singer-songwriter jeremy messersmith neatly sums up what can happen when your friends have kids. This performance was recorded live outside Surly Brewing Co. in Minneapolis just before The Current's Happy Hour event on Thursday, Aug. 14, 2025.

Musician
jeremy messersmith – vocals, guitar

Credits
Guest – @jeremymessersmith 
Video and audio – Evan Clark
Graphics – Natalia Toledo
Digital Production – Luke Taylor
title: jeremy messersmith plays "Twenty Years" outside Surly Brewing in Minneapolis

To celebrate The Current’s 20th Anniversary, The Current’s Live Sessions Vault unlocks never-before-seen live performance videos of bands and artists who have played in our iconic studio. 

Watch to see the full session of Blitzen Trapper, featuring previously unreleased footage, from when they visited The Current studio back in 2015.

00:04:05 Love Grow Cold
